<ns5606:section xmlns:ns5606="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.concepts.architecture.patterns.modelViewController.context">

  <ns5607:title xmlns:ns5607="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Context</ns5607:title>
  <ns5608:para xmlns:ns5608="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    Systems typically receive a high rate of user-interface change requests. Furthermore,
    <ns5609:itemizedlist xmlns:ns5609="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      <ns5610:listitem xmlns:ns5610="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns5611:para xmlns:ns5611="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        most extensions made to systems require corresponding changes in the user interface,
      </ns5611:para></ns5610:listitem>
      <ns5612:listitem xmlns:ns5612="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns5613:para xmlns:ns5613="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        at times the same business logic may need to be accessed via different user interfaces
        (for example, desktop GUI, web-based user-interface, and from mobile platforms like
        mobile phones and PDAs),
      </ns5613:para></ns5612:listitem>
      <ns5614:listitem xmlns:ns5614="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns5615:para xmlns:ns5615="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        when a system is ported from one platform to another, one may need to use a different
        user interface realization,
      </ns5615:para></ns5614:listitem>
      <ns5616:listitem xmlns:ns5616="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns5617:para xmlns:ns5617="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        different role players may want to obtain different views onto the same information, and
      </ns5617:para></ns5616:listitem>
      <ns5618:listitem xmlns:ns5618="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns5619:para xmlns:ns5619="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        users may want to change the look and feel or at times even the functionality which is
        accessible through the user interface.
      </ns5619:para></ns5618:listitem>
    </ns5609:itemizedlist>
  </ns5608:para>
</ns5606:section>